<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Practical_estimation_of_alc=
ohol_content">Practical estimation of alcohol content</h2><span class=3D"mw=
-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAlcohol_by_volume&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Practical estimation of alcohol =
content"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gravity_(alcoholic_b=
everage)" title=3D"Gravity (alcoholic beverage)">Gravity (alcoholic beverag=
e)</a></div>
<p>During the production of wine and beer, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Yeast" title=3D"Yeast">yeast</a> is added to a sugary solution. Du=
ring fermentation, the yeasts consume the sugars and produce alcohol. The d=
ensity of sugar in water is greater than the density of alcohol in water. A=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrometer" title=3D"Hydrometer">=
hydrometer</a> is used to measure the change in <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Specific_gravity" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Specific gra=
vity">specific gravity</a> (SG) of the solution before and after fermentati=
on. The volume of alcohol in the solution can then be estimated.  There are=
 a number of empirical formulae which brewers and winemakers use to estimat=
e the alcohol content of the liquor made.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Templ=
ate Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation n=
eeded"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (Oct=
ober 2024)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p>Specific gravity is the density of a liquid relative to that of wate=
r, i.e., if the density of the liquid is 1.05 times that of water, it has a=
 specific gravity of 1.05. In UK brewing usage, it is customary to regard t=
he reference value for water to be 1000, so the specific gravity of the sam=
e example beer would be quoted as 1050. The formulas here assume that the f=
ormer definition is used for specific gravity.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-=
Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citat=
ion needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources.=
 (October 2024)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"General">General</h3><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAlcohol_by_volume&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: General"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>During <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethanol_fermentation" ti=
tle=3D"Ethanol fermentation">ethanol fermentation</a> the yeast converts on=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mole_(unit)" title=3D"Mole (unit=
)">mole</a> of sugar into two moles of alcohol. A general formula for calcu=
lating the resulting alcohol concentration by volume can be written:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ABV=3DSBVfermented\times GECF}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mi>e</mi>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mi>G</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mi>F</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ABV=3DSBVferm=
ented\times GECF}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ddb1cac12db67632d1eba35b7e21006a5ebc1605" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:34.461ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle AB=
V=3DSBVfermented\times GECF}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where SBV fermented is sugar by volume (g/dL) converted to alcohol durin=
g fermentation and GECF is the glucose-ethanol conversion factor:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e GECF=3D{\frac {2\times 46.069}{180.156}}\approx 0.511435}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>G</mi>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mi>F</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>46.069</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mn>180.156</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=89=88<!-- =E2=89=88 --></mo>
        <mn>0.511435</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle GECF=3D{\frac=
 {2\times 46.069}{180.156}}\approx 0.511435}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fc509d476b6ab59a3a642f37b6c3218a4c841412" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:33.389ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle GE=
CF=3D{\frac {2\times 46.069}{180.156}}\approx 0.511435}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where 46.069 is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molar_mass"=
 title=3D"Molar mass">molar mass</a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Ethanol" title=3D"Ethanol">ethanol</a> and 180.156 is the molar mass =
of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glucose" title=3D"Glucose">gluc=
ose</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fructose" title=3D"Fru=
ctose">fructose</a>.
</p>
