n></dd></dl>
<p>SG drop is how much the SG decreased during fermentation (at 20 degree C=
). The factor 135 is most accurate in the center of the SG drop range of 0.=
000 to 0.179. Since the correlation of SG and Brix is non-linear it is comm=
on to divide the range to increase accuracy when using the simple ABV formu=
la:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e ABV\approx factor\times SGdrop}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=88<!-- =E2=89=88 --></mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mi>c</mi>
