<p>Example ABV calculation:
</p>
<ul><li>SG measured at start of fermentation 1.067</li>
<li>SG measured at end of fermentation 1.007</li>
<li>SG drop =3D 1.067 - 1.007 =3D 0.06</li>
<li>Factor from table above 134</li>
<li>ABV =3D 134 x 0.06 =3D 8.04</li></ul>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Advanced">Advanced</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAlcohol_by_volume&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Advanced"><span>edi=
t</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Advanced formula derived from Carl Balling empirical formulas.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-21" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Alcohol_by_volume#cite_note-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The formula compensates for cha=
nges in SG with changes in alcohol concentration and for the fact that not =
all sugar is converted into alcohol. All values are measured at 20 degree C=
.
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle ABV=3D{\frac {-118772\times {\text{SG final}}\times ({\=
text{Plato start}}-{\text{Plato final}})}{({\text{Plato start}}-193.765)\ti=
mes ({\text{Plato start}}+1220)}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>118772</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>SG final</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Plato start</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Plato final</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Plato start</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>193.765</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>Plato start</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>1220</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ABV=3D{\frac =
{-118772\times {\text{SG final}}\times ({\text{Plato start}}-{\text{Plato f=
inal}})}{({\text{Plato start}}-193.765)\times ({\text{Plato start}}+1220)}}=
}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7577590bed638f3cd0129b315aee04324561be60" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:57.84ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle AB=
V=3D{\frac {-118772\times {\text{SG final}}\times ({\text{Plato start}}-{\t=
ext{Plato final}})}{({\text{Plato start}}-193.765)\times ({\text{Plato star=
t}}+1220)}}}"></span>
</p><p>where SG final is the specific gravity when fermentation ends, Plato=
 start is the sugar by weight when fermentation begins, Plato final is the =
sugar by weight when fermentation ends. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Brix" title=3D"Brix">Brix</a> can be used instead of Plato as they ar=
e nearly identical.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Wine">Wine</h3><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAlcohol_by_volume&amp;acti=
on=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Wine"><span>edit</span></=
a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The simplest method for wine has been described by English author <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyril_Berry" title=3D"Cyril Berry">Cyril=
 Berry</a>:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBerry1998_22-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_by_volume#cite_note-FOOTNO=
